    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the separation between religion and public policy",
        "additional_details": "We would like:\r\nAn end to Bishops and archbishops sitting as members of the House of Lords without being democratically elected.\r\nAn end to state funding of religious schools. \r\n \r\nThis is currently all being paid for by the taxpayer.",
        "background": "Only 16% of the UK is actually Church of England Protestant. In 2019, the taxpayer can no longer subsidize religion. \r\nWe are calling for more separation between religion and the state. \r\n",
